    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9759" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὧδε</span></b>  (adv. from <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅδε</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">so, thus, in this way</span>,
          referring either to what follows or to what precedes, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.181</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            7.34</span></i>; correl. to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὡς, Γ 300</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 6.477</span></i>; like <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὔτως, ὧδε θέεις ἀκίχητα διώκων</span>, ‘just as you
          do,’ i. e. in vain, <i><span class="en">Il. 17.75</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.12</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">just, as you
          see</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.182</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.28</span></i> (according to Aristarchus <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὧδε</span> never means <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hither</span> in
          Homer); <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">to such a degree</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            12.346</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
